msgctxt "100_Kiryu"
msgid "Yasuko-san. You keep saying you owe Taiga your life."
msgstr "Yasuko-san. You keep saying you owe Taiga your life."

msgctxt "112_Kiryu"
msgid "And I get it. We all rely on other people. It's hard to keep\\r\n"\n"going without someone loving you, supporting you, pushing you onward."
msgstr "Y lo entiendo. Todos dependemos de otras personas. Es difícil\\r seguir adelante sin alguien que te quiera, te apoye y te impulse a seguir adelante."

msgctxt "124_Kiryu"
msgid "But in your case, Taiga became more than that. He's not just\\r\n"\n"your support. He's your reason to keep living."
msgstr "But in your case, Taiga became more than that. He's not just\\r\n"\n"your support. He's your reason to keep living."

msgctxt "136_Yasuko"
msgid "I..."
msgstr "Yo..."

msgctxt "148_Kiryu"
msgid "I know life hasn't been easy for you. Losing your parents is\\r\n"\n"one of the worst pains imaginable, and you had to bear that\\r\n"\n"burden at a far younger age than most."
msgstr "I know life hasn't been easy for you. Losing your parents is\\r\n"\n"one of the worst pains imaginable, and you had to bear that\\r\n"\n"burden at a far younger age than most."

msgctxt "160_Kiryu"
msgid "But having a hard life doesn't excuse the way you've lived."
msgstr "But having a hard life doesn't excuse the way you've lived."

msgctxt "172_Yasuko"
msgid "Ngh..."
msgstr "Ngh..."

msgctxt "184_Kiryu"
msgid "Not that I have any right to talk. I've made my fair share\\r\n"\n"of mistakes."
msgstr "Not that I have any right to talk. I've made my fair share\\r\n"\n"of mistakes."

msgctxt "196_Date"
msgid "Kiryu..."
msgstr "Kiryu..."

msgctxt "208_Yasuko"
msgid "......"
msgstr "......"

msgctxt "220_Kiryu"
msgid "I understand why you feel so strongly, but that emotion has\\r\n"\n"led you to some bad decisions."
msgstr "I understand why you feel so strongly, but that emotion has\\r\n"\n"led you to some bad decisions."

msgctxt "232_Kiryu"
msgid "It's not a stretch to say it's completely clouded your judgment."
msgstr "It's not a stretch to say it's completely clouded your judgment."

msgctxt "244_Kiryu"
msgid "So, I need you to stay here while I go figure out where your\\r\n"\n"brother is. It's for your own good."
msgstr "So, I need you to stay here while I go figure out where your\\r\n"\n"brother is. It's for your own good."

msgctxt "256_Yasuko"
msgid "But..."
msgstr "Pero..."

msgctxt "268_Date"
msgid "Kiryu..."
msgstr "Kiryu..."

msgctxt "280_Kiryu"
msgid "Don't worry, I'll find him. And I'll make sure you two are\\r\n"\n"reunited. I promise."
msgstr "Don't worry, I'll find him. And I'll make sure you two are\\r\n"\n"reunited. I promise."

msgctxt "292_Kiryu"
msgid "But for now, you just need to be patient. Okay?"
msgstr "But for now, you just need to be patient. Okay?"

msgctxt "304_Yasuko"
msgid "...Yes. Thank you."
msgstr "...Yes. Thank you."

msgctxt "316_Kiryu"
msgid "Thank you, Yasuko-san."
msgstr "Thank you, Yasuko-san."

msgctxt "340_Kiryu"
msgid "Take care of her for me, will you?"
msgstr "Take care of her for me, will you?"

msgctxt "352_Date"
msgid "Heh, do you even have to ask?"
msgstr "Heh, do you even have to ask?"

msgctxt "412_Yasuko"
msgid "So, what is it you want to ask me?"
msgstr "So, what is it you want to ask me?"

msgctxt "424_Kiryu"
msgid "Sorry if this is a blunt question..."
msgstr "Sorry if this is a blunt question..."

msgctxt "436_Kiryu"
msgid "But why do you need to see your brother so bad? Bad enough\\r\n"\n"to murder for it?"
msgstr "But why do you need to see your brother so bad? Bad enough\\r\n"\n"to murder for it?"

msgctxt "448_Date"
msgid "Wait, you what!?"
msgstr "Wait, you what!?"

msgctxt "460_Yasuko"
msgid "Kiryu-san, is this really the best place to..."
msgstr "Kiryu-san, is this really the best place to..."

msgctxt "472_Kiryu"
msgid "Don't worry about Date-san. He's an ex-detective, yeah, but\\r\n"\n"we can trust him. I promise."
msgstr "Don't worry about Date-san. He's an ex-detective, yeah, but\\r\n"\n"we can trust him. I promise."

msgctxt "484_Kiryu"
msgid "He'd never turn you in without hearing what you had to say\\r\n"\n"first."
msgstr "He'd never turn you in without hearing what you had to say\\r\n"\n"first."

msgctxt "496_Kiryu"
msgid "Isn't that right, Date-san?"
msgstr "Isn't that right, Date-san?"

msgctxt "508_Date"
msgid "Well, uh... Yeah, that's right."
msgstr "Well, uh... Yeah, that's right."

msgctxt "520_Kiryu"
msgid "Now tell me the truth, Yasuko-san. Why would you go so far\\r\n"\n"for your brother?"
msgstr "Now tell me the truth, Yasuko-san. Why would you go so far\\r\n"\n"for your brother?"

msgctxt "532_Yasuko"
msgid "I..."
msgstr "Yo..."

msgctxt "544_Kiryu"
msgid "Yasuko-san."
msgstr "Yasuko-san."

msgctxt "556_Date"
msgid "C'mon."
msgstr "C'mon."

msgctxt "568_Yasuko"
msgid "It's because... because Taiga is everything to me. I owe him\\r\n"\n"my life."
msgstr "It's because... because Taiga is everything to me. I owe him\\r\n"\n"my life."

msgctxt "580_Kiryu"
msgid "What?"
msgstr "¿Qué?"

msgctxt "592_Yasuko"
msgid "I'm serious. If it weren't for him, I would have died years\\r\n"\n"ago."
msgstr "I'm serious. If it weren't for him, I would have died years\\r\n"\n"ago."

msgctxt "604_Kiryu"
msgid "Go on."
msgstr "Dime."

msgctxt "616_Yasuko"
msgid "Have you ever heard of a living-donor kidney transplant?"
msgstr "Have you ever heard of a living-donor kidney transplant?"

msgctxt "628_Date"
msgid "Oh yeah, you read about those things all the time. That's\\r\n"\n"when they give you a kidney from one of your relatives,\\r\n"\n"right? They say you only need one, after all."
msgstr "Oh yeah, you read about those things all the time. That's\\r\n"\n"when they give you a kidney from one of your relatives,\\r\n"\n"right? They say you only need one, after all."

msgctxt "640_Yasuko"
msgid "Right. The truth of it is... I'm the recipient of one of those\\r\n"\n"living-donor transplants."
msgstr "Right. The truth of it is... I'm the recipient of one of those\\r\n"\n"living-donor transplants."

msgctxt "652_Date"
msgid "And your brother's the one who gave it to you, huh?"
msgstr "And your brother's the one who gave it to you, huh?"

msgctxt "664_Kiryu"
msgid "That's what you meant when you said you owe him your life."
msgstr "That's what you meant when you said you owe him your life."

msgctxt "676_Yasuko"
msgid "...Yes."
msgstr "...Yes."

msgctxt "688_Date"
msgid "Hold on. Getting a transplant like that from your sibling\\r\n"\n"isn't all that uncommon."
msgstr "Hold on. Getting a transplant like that from your sibling\\r\n"\n"isn't all that uncommon."

msgctxt "700_Date"
msgid "I'm not judging or anything, but do you really owe him that\\r\n"\n"much just for a kidney?"
msgstr "I'm not judging or anything, but do you really owe him that\\r\n"\n"much just for a kidney?"

msgctxt "712_Yasuko"
msgid "It's not that simple."
msgstr "It's not that simple."

msgctxt "724_Kiryu"
msgid "Think you can explain?"
msgstr "Think you can explain?"

msgctxt "736_Yasuko"
msgid "The kidney I got... It wasn't Taiga's. He wasn't a match."
msgstr "The kidney I got... It wasn't Taiga's. He wasn't a match."

msgctxt "748_Date"
msgid "What, different blood types?"
msgstr "What, different blood types?"

msgctxt "760_Yasuko"
msgid "Well, yes, but..."
msgstr "Well, yes, but..."

msgctxt "772_Date"
msgid "But what? Why couldn't you get the transplant from your brother?"
msgstr "But what? Why couldn't you get the transplant from your brother?"

msgctxt "784_Kiryu"
msgid "...Yasuko-san?"
msgstr "...Yasuko-san?"

msgctxt "796_Yasuko"
msgid "I, um..."
msgstr "I, um..."

msgctxt "808_Kiryu"
msgid "I think I get what's going on here. You and Taiga aren't\\r\n"\n"actually siblings."
msgstr "I think I get what's going on here. You and Taiga aren't\\r\n"\n"actually siblings."

msgctxt "820_Date"
msgid "Kiryu!"
msgstr "¡Kiryu!"

msgctxt "832_Yasuko"
msgid "He's right. Taiga is my stepfather's son from his prior\\r\n"\n"marriage, while my mother had me before she and my\\r\n"\n"stepfather ever even met."
msgstr "He's right. Taiga is my stepfather's son from his prior\\r\n"\n"marriage, while my mother had me before she and my\\r\n"\n"stepfather ever even met."

msgctxt "844_Date"
msgid "Then where'd you find a match?"
msgstr "Then where'd you find a match?"

msgctxt "856_Yasuko"
msgid "Since my mother had already passed... Taiga tracked down my\\r\n"\n"biological father and begged him to donate his kidney to me."
msgstr "Since my mother had already passed... Taiga tracked down my\\r\n"\n"biological father and begged him to donate his kidney to me."

msgctxt "868_Kiryu"
msgid "Saejima..."
msgstr "Saejima..."

msgctxt "880_Yasuko"
msgid "Beyond the regular difficulty of finding a kidney donor, my\\r\n"\n"blood type is extremely rare. A direct relative was my only\\r\n"\n"hope of a match."
msgstr "Beyond the regular difficulty of finding a kidney donor, my\\r\n"\n"blood type is extremely rare. A direct relative was my only\\r\n"\n"hope of a match."

msgctxt "892_Yasuko"
msgid "Once Taiga learned that, he spent every waking moment of his\\r\n"\n"life scouring the city until he found my father."
msgstr "Once Taiga learned that, he spent every waking moment of his\\r\n"\n"life scouring the city until he found my father."

msgctxt "904_Yasuko"
msgid "He was only 15 years old at the time."
msgstr "He was only 15 years old at the time."

msgctxt "916_Date"
msgid "Still just a kid, huh..."
msgstr "Still just a kid, huh..."

msgctxt "928_Yasuko"
msgid "I had honestly given up hope. Before my mother died, she\\r\n"\n"told me my father was nothing more than an abusive drunk\\r\n"\n"with no chance of ever changing."
msgstr "I had honestly given up hope. Before my mother died, she\\r\n"\n"told me my father was nothing more than an abusive drunk\\r\n"\n"with no chance of ever changing."

msgctxt "940_Yasuko"
msgid "Based on what I knew, it seemed likely he was already dead.\\r\n"\n"Even if he wasn't, I didn't want to live knowing I owed my\\r\n"\n"life to such a horrible man."
msgstr "Based on what I knew, it seemed likely he was already dead.\\r\n"\n"Even if he wasn't, I didn't want to live knowing I owed my\\r\n"\n"life to such a horrible man."

msgctxt "952_Yasuko"
msgid "At the time, I would have rather died than continue on\\r\n"\n"carrying a part of him inside me."
msgstr "At the time, I would have rather died than continue on\\r\n"\n"carrying a part of him inside me."

msgctxt "964_Kiryu"
msgid "......"
msgstr "......"

msgctxt "976_Yasuko"
msgid "But Taiga wouldn't take no for an answer. He said no matter\\r\n"\n"what happened, he would take care of me."
msgstr "But Taiga wouldn't take no for an answer. He said no matter\\r\n"\n"what happened, he would take care of me."

msgctxt "988_Date"
msgid "Then... he found your dad?"
msgstr "Then... he found your dad?"

msgctxt "1000_Yasuko"
msgid "Yes."
msgstr "Sí."

msgctxt "1012_Date"
msgid "Well? Where was he?"
msgstr "Well? Where was he?"

msgctxt "1024_Yasuko"
msgid "In Kansai. He had started working for a yakuza organization\\r\n"\n"called the Omi Alliance. Handling the dirty jobs nobody else\\r\n"\n"wanted to touch."
msgstr "In Kansai. He had started working for a yakuza organization\\r\n"\n"called the Omi Alliance. Handling the dirty jobs nobody else\\r\n"\n"wanted to touch."

msgctxt "1036_Date"
msgid "The Omi!?"
msgstr "The Omi!?"

msgctxt "1048_Yasuko"
msgid "That's right. Taiga went alone to Kansai, knowing full well\\r\n"\n"that my father was a yakuza, but..."
msgstr "That's right. Taiga went alone to Kansai, knowing full well\\r\n"\n"that my father was a yakuza, but..."

msgctxt "1060_Kiryu"
msgid "Let me guess. They tried to extort him."
msgstr "Let me guess. They tried to extort him."

msgctxt "1072_Yasuko"
msgid "Exactly. A yakuza through and through, my father demanded\\r\n"\n"a massive sum of money in exchange for one of his kidneys."
msgstr "Exactly. A yakuza through and through, my father demanded\\r\n"\n"a massive sum of money in exchange for one of his kidneys."

msgctxt "1084_Date"
msgid "How much cash are we talking here?"
msgstr "How much cash are we talking here?"

msgctxt "1096_Yasuko"
msgid "Thirty million yen."
msgstr "Thirty million yen."

msgctxt "1108_Date"
msgid "Thirty mil!? That's a ton now, but it was a fortune back then! How was a kid ever supposed to get his hands on that kind of money!?"
msgstr "Thirty mil!? That's a ton now, but it was a fortune back then! How was a kid ever supposed to get his hands on that kind of money!?"

msgctxt "1120_Yasuko"
msgid "He wasn't. That was the point."
msgstr "He wasn't. That was the point."

msgctxt "1132_Yasuko"
msgid "But Taiga didn't give up. He started fighting thugs in the\\r\n"\n"streets of Kamurocho, trying to scrape together whatever\\r\n"\n"funds he could."
msgstr "But Taiga didn't give up. He started fighting thugs in the\\r\n"\n"streets of Kamurocho, trying to scrape together whatever\\r\n"\n"funds he could."

msgctxt "1144_Date"
msgid "That would never work. Not for cash like that."
msgstr "That would never work. Not for cash like that."

msgctxt "1156_Yasuko"
msgid "It didn't. Not until Sasai-san from the Tojo Clan stepped\\r\n"\n"in."
msgstr "It didn't. Not until Sasai-san from the Tojo Clan stepped\\r\n"\n"in."

msgctxt "1168_Yasuko"
msgid "He gave Taiga the thirty million under one condition: he\\r\n"\n"join the Sasai Family."
msgstr "He gave Taiga the thirty million under one condition: he\\r\n"\n"join the Sasai Family."

msgctxt "1180_Kiryu"
msgid "So that's how he ended up in the Tojo."
msgstr "So that's how he ended up in the Tojo."

msgctxt "1192_Yasuko"
msgid "All that time, Taiga never turned his back to me. Even when\\r\n"\n"it seemed like all hope was lost, he supported me."
msgstr "All that time, Taiga never turned his back to me. Even when\\r\n"\n"it seemed like all hope was lost, he supported me."

msgctxt "1204_Yasuko"
msgid "He dropped out of high school, gave up on his dream of\\r\n"\n"becoming a teacher, even joined the yakuza for me..."
msgstr "He dropped out of high school, gave up on his dream of\\r\n"\n"becoming a teacher, even joined the yakuza for me..."

msgctxt "1216_Kiryu"
msgid "So that's what you meant when you said you owe him your\\r\n"\n"life."
msgstr "So that's what you meant when you said you owe him your\\r\n"\n"life."

msgctxt "1228_Yasuko"
msgid "That's right. He's everything to me."
msgstr "That's right. He's everything to me."

msgctxt "1240_Yasuko"
msgid "Not only did Taiga literally save my life, but he gave me\\r\n"\n"the will to keep on living."
msgstr "Not only did Taiga literally save my life, but he gave me\\r\n"\n"the will to keep on living."

msgctxt "1252_Kiryu"
msgid "Yasuko-san..."
msgstr "Yasuko-san..."

msgctxt "1276_Date"
msgid "What's going on, Kiryu? You show up in a guy's bar and don't even drop him a line first?"
msgstr "What's going on, Kiryu? You show up in a guy's bar and don't even drop him a line first?"

msgctxt "1288_Kiryu"
msgid "Sorry for not letting you know, Date-san. I have some business in town."
msgstr "Sorry for not letting you know, Date-san. I have some business in town."

msgctxt "1300_Date"
msgid "...Work never ends for the ex-fourth chairman, huh?"
msgstr "...Work never ends for the ex-fourth chairman, huh?"

msgctxt "1312_Kiryu"
msgid "You've got that right. Anyway, this is Yasuko Saejima. I'm\\r\n"\n"here helping her with a little something."
msgstr "You've got that right. Anyway, this is Yasuko Saejima. I'm\\r\n"\n"here helping her with a little something."

msgctxt "1324_Yasuko"
msgid "It's nice to meet you."
msgstr "It's nice to meet you."

msgctxt "1336_Date"
msgid "Oh, the pleasure's all mine."
msgstr "Oh, the pleasure's all mine."

msgctxt "1348_Date"
msgid "She's a knockout, Kiryu. How'd you end up bringing a girl\\r\n"\n"like her back here, huh?"
msgstr "She's a knockout, Kiryu. How'd you end up bringing a girl\\r\n"\n"like her back here, huh?"

msgctxt "1360_Kiryu"
msgid "Whatever you're thinking, I guarantee you've got the wrong\\r\n"\n"idea. Let's leave it at that."
msgstr "Whatever you're thinking, I guarantee you've got the wrong\\r\n"\n"idea. Let's leave it at that."

msgctxt "1372_Kiryu"
msgid "By the way, where's Mama?"
msgstr "By the way, where's Mama?"

msgctxt "1384_Date"
msgid "Gone for the week. Family trouble, you know how it goes."
msgstr "Gone for the week. Family trouble, you know how it goes."

msgctxt "1396_Kiryu"
msgid "And you're holding down the fort while she's gone?"
msgstr "And you're holding down the fort while she's gone?"

msgctxt "1408_Date"
msgid "Yup. It's a real pain, what with my other work and all, but\\r\n"\n"she insists we keep it open for the regulars."
msgstr "Yup. It's a real pain, what with my other work and all, but\\r\n"\n"she insists we keep it open for the regulars."

msgctxt "1420_Kiryu"
msgid "Lucky for us that she does."
msgstr "Lucky for us that she does."

msgctxt "1432_Date"
msgid "Now, Kiryu. What's this \"little something\" you need to take\\r\n"\n"care of?"
msgstr "Now, Kiryu. What's this \"little something\" you need to take\\r\n"\n"care of?"

msgctxt "1444_Kiryu"
msgid "Oh, right. You mind taking a seat, Yasuko-san?"
msgstr "Oh, right. You mind taking a seat, Yasuko-san?"

msgctxt "1456_Yasuko"
msgid "Um..."
msgstr "Em..."

msgctxt "1468_Kiryu"
msgid "Please. I just need to ask you something before we head out\\r\n"\n"to find your brother."
msgstr "Please. I just need to ask you something before we head out\\r\n"\n"to find your brother."

msgctxt "1480_Yasuko"
msgid "...Okay."
msgstr "...Bien."

